The late Apostle Chiriseri and wife Pastor Petunia ChiriseriLEADER of His Presence Ministries International, Apostle Charles Chiriseri, passed away early this morning in a road accident in Mbembesi, Matabeleland North province. Reports say Apostle Chiriseri died on the spot while his wife, Pastor Petunia, is currently admitted in a Bulawayo hospital. An official from the church confirmed the sad news but said details are still sketchy. The official said the Chiriseris were traveling back from a funeral when tragedy struck in Mbembesi.Apostle Charles and his wife co-founded His Presence Ministries International in 2006. Prior to that, he was a senior pastor at Faith Ministries.The couple has four biological and five adopted children.More details to follow: 